spring boot, spring boot security, spring data, thymeleaf, Gradle, and postgresql

command :

- how to run this application :
    - go to your project root
    - type command : gradle bootRun

Database (Postgresql)

 you can use PgAdmin, it will be easier to manage the database.
 database source available in /src/main/resources/db_script/.
 - create database first, (blog_app_1) that is my database name on application.properties
 - execute all database source.
 - test the application
